author: Emily Glazer
title: Wells Fargo’s Results: 5 Things to Watch
text:
Wells Fargo & Co., the third-biggest U.S. bank by assets, is expected to report its fourth-quarter results before the market opens Friday. Here’s what you need to know.
1. Higher Earnings Expected
Analysts are expecting Wells Fargo to post per-share earnings of $1.06 for the quarter, according to Thomson Reuters, compared with 96 cents...
